I'm a little confused by this, so let me try and spell it out. Correct me if I'm wrong:

Skip is a humanoid made out of ash shavings.
It eats corpses. The method for how it does this was the most confusing part of the article.
The person who used to be this thing escaped some African cult that likely put some kind of spirit/monster/demon in them, for the express purpose of being consumed by it.
Person didn't jive with this, so they escaped to England and have been trying to contain themselves until something awoke the demon.
I don't know where the tongue thing fits in narratively, but I liked it. The description could use some serious cleanup, as could much of this article, and if you took out the bit about why it curled up afterward, you'd be showing a lot more.


So is this an original article with new stuff, an original article rewritten, or a completely new article?

